<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 James F. Hurley has been named executive vice president for investor relations 
and corporate communications at California Federal Bank. 
</P>
<P>
 Hurley, who previously served as senior vice president of the Los Angeles bank 
and its former parent company, CalFed Inc., is responsible for communicating 
the bank's strategies, policies and financial performance to the investment 
community, the financial media and the public. 
</P>
<P>
 N. Christian Anderson, associate publisher and former editor of the Orange 
County Register, will become publisher of the Colorado Springs Gazette 
Telegraph, a daily newspaper owned by Irvine-based Freedom Newspapers Inc., the 
Register's parent company. The Colorado Springs newspaper has a daily 
circulation of 101,000. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Anita Realty Enterprises Inc. said it has named Brian Fleming chief 
financial officer and executive vice president. 
</P>
<P>
 Before coming to Arcadia-based Santa Anita, Fleming was with Carter Hawley 
Hale Stores Inc. He was an audit manager with Price Waterhouse before that. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Anita Cos., through Santa Anita Realty and Santa Anita Operating Co., 
operates the Santa Anita racetrack and holds interests in two major regional 
shopping centers, strip malls and office buildings. 
</P>
<P>
 Dennis Robinson has been appointed president and chief executive of Citadel 
Financial Group. 
</P>
<P>
 Before joining the Los Angeles-based lender, which specializes in purchasing 
loan portfolios, Robinson was a senior vice president at Foothill Group. 
</P>
</TEXT>
