<P>
EL TORO, CALVARY CHAPEL ATOP BRACKETS IN SECTION VOLLEYBALL PLAYOFFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 El Toro and Calvary Chapel are top-seeded in Division I and Division III of 
the Southern Section boys' volleyball playoff pairings announced Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 El Toro (15-1), top-ranked in Orange County, has a first-round bye.The 
Chargers will play the Corona del Mar-Estancia winner in the second round May 
17. 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach (13-1), ranked second in the county and second-seeded in Division 
I, is home to Tustin (10-6), an at-large entry, in the first round at 7 p.m. 
Friday.  
</P>
<P>
 Marina (9-9) also has an at-large berth in Division I and will play 
third-seeded Los Angeles Loyola (17-1) in the first round Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Esperanza (14-2), ranked fourth in the county, is third-seeded in Division II. 
The Aztecs play host to Redlands Arrowhead Christian (9-6) in the first round 
Friday.  
</P>
<P>
 Calvary Chapel (14-0), No. 6 in the county, has a first-round bye and will 
play the Pasadena Poly-San Marino Southwestern Academy winner in Round 2. 
Whittier Christian (12-3) is third-seeded in Division III and hosts Downey Pius 
X (8-5) in the first round Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Alamitos (8-11) will play host to La Quinta (10-6) in a Division II 
wild-card match at 7 p.m. Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Finals in all three divisions are set May 28 at Cerritos College. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Garden Grove is seeded third and Marina fourth in the Southern Section 
Division I badminton pairings. 
</P>
<P>
 Ocean View (9-4) plays host to Costa Mesa (5-6) in a wild-card match at 3 p.m. 
Wednesday. The winner advances to the first round May 17 at Garden Grove 
(12-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton (7-8) plays host to La Quinta (5-5) in a wild-card match Wednesday. 
The winner advances to play Marina (14-1). 
</P>
<P>
 The finals are set May 25 at Cypress College. 
</P>
<P>
 * PLAYOFF PAIRINGS: C9 
</P>
