<P>
PREP PLAYOFFS AT GLANCE; CITY SECTION BOYS' TEAM TENNIS FINALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG SANDOVAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Today's pairings (at Studio City Raquet Center): Woodland Hills Taft (14-0), 
last year's Division 4-A runner-up, takes on University (15-0), at 2 p.m. Van 
Nuys (13-1), last year's 3-A runner-up, plays Bell (16-0) in the other 
championship match. 
</P>
<P>
 * Last year's finish: Led by No. 1 singles player Rafael Huerta, Chatsworth 
defeated Taft, 19 1/2-10, for the 4-A title, while Marshall won its third 
consecutive 3-A title by defeating Van Nuys 18 1/2-11. 
</P>
<P>
 * Outlook: University sends a senior-dominated team against a Taft squad 
without any seniors playing singles. Taft's top two singles players are 
sophomore Dylan Mann and freshman Golan Sassoon. "Mann is probably the best 
singles player in the city," said Tom Anderson, University's coach. University, 
which won the 4-A title in 1992, is led by No 1 singles player Jay Jackson. In 
the 3-A final, Van Nuys is led by No. 1 singles player Steve Park, who 
transferred from Granada Hills this year. Bell has won 85 of 91 individual 
matches this season and is led by No. 1 player Jose Cardenas and the No. 1 
doubles team of Jose Ruiz and Oscar De La Rosa. GREG SANDOVAL 
</P>
