<HEADLINE>
<P>
CYPRESS TOP-SEEDED IN BASEBALL PLAYOFFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cypress, the Orange Empire Conference champion, is the top-seeded baseball 
team in the Southern California playoff pairings, which were announced Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress (34-10) plays host to East Los Angeles (22-18) in the best-of-three 
series starting at noon Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Riverside, the second-place team in the Orange Empire Conference, third-place 
Rancho Santiago and fourth-place Saddleback also made the playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Santiago is the defending State champion. Cypress won the title in 
1991. 
</P>
<P>
 Riverside (31-9), the No. 6-seeded team, plays host to No. 11 Cerritos 
(27-13); No. 10 Rancho Santiago (32-11) is at No. 7 Los Angeles Mission (26-15) 
and No. 12 Saddleback (23-14-1) is at No. 5 Cuesta (32-11). 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles Harbor (29-12), the No. 2-seeded team, plays host to No. 15 L.A. 
Pierce (26-15); No. 14 San Diego Mesa (22-13-1) is at No. 3 Citrus (32-5); No. 
13 Bakersfield (25-16) is at No. 4 Southwestern (34-7-1) and No. 9 Chaffey 
(33-8) is at No. 8 Mt. San Antonio (27-14). 
</P>
<P>
 The eight winners advance to the second round May 20-22. Two teams move on to 
the State tournament May 28-30 at Cerritos College. STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
