<HEADLINE>
<P>
DOWN TIME; AH, TIME FOR A PARENTAL LULLABY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Down Time starts at bedtime. The kids' bedtime. Time to relax and pad 
downstairs for a cup of tea.Feet up, television on, splayed out on our comfy 
green sofa with a steaming cup of tea melting the day away. Perhaps a decadent 
snack we've managed to hide from the kids. Peace and quiet, a little 
conversation with the man I love. 
</P>
<P>
 My husband and I chat about our day, emptying our minds of worries and cares. 
Tea mug in hand, uninterrupted by bellowing toddlers or chatty salesmen, I can 
think. Such is bliss . . . until the midnight feeding. 
</P>
<P>
 -- HELENE LESEL 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
