<P>
VENTURA COUNTY REVIEW: COUNTY BUILDING COMES ON STRONG IN 1ST QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jack Searles 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Continuing the recent comeback in real estate and construction, building 
projects in Ventura County totaled $123.5 million in the first quarter, up 41% 
from the first three months of 1993.It's the strongest first-quarter 
performance since 1990, according to the Construction Industry Research Board. 
</P>
<P>
 Residential projects in the first quarter amounted to $74.1 million, up 54% 
from a year earlier, while commercial and industrial construction totaled $49.3 
million, up 26%. 
