<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY REVIEW: 2 LOCAL FIRMS TO INSTALL SOLAR-RUN PHONE SWITCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jack Searles 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two Ventura County firms -- Siemens Solar Industries and GTE California -- 
have joined in installing North America's first solar-powered telephone routing 
switch. 
</P>
<P>
 The unit, called a digital loop carrier, will bring phone service to a remote 
cluster of 20 homes in San Bernardino County.The community has no commercial 
electrical service and no available telephone lines. A solar, or photovoltaic, 
unit was chosen to power the switch because it would have been too costly to 
run electrical and telephone lines to the area. 
</P>
<P>
 Siemens Solar, based in Camarillo, provided the solar cells used in a special 
switch produced by a sister company, Siemens Stromberg-Carlson. GTE California, 
based in Thousand Oaks, said it is considering solar-powered switches as "an 
ideal solution" for meeting rural customers' needs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
