<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: ST. IVES LABORATORIES PROFIT DECLINES 45% 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 St. Ives Laboratories Inc., a Chatsworth-based maker of skin-care products, 
said its first-quarter profits for the three months that ended March 31 were 
$488,000, down 45% from $890,000 for the same period the previous year. Revenue 
in the first quarter was $42.65 million, up 8% from $39.54 million the year 
before. 
</P>
<P>
 The company attributed the results to increased selling expenses and the cost 
of repairing facilities damaged in the Northridge earthquake. 
</P>
