<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: INCOMNET REPORTS $598,945 QUARTERLY PROFIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Incomnet Inc., a Woodland Hills telecommunications company, reported a profit 
of $598,945 for the first quarter that ended March 31, rebounding from a loss 
of $1.1 million in the same period a year earlier. The profit was on a record 
first-quarter revenue of $7.89 million, an increase of more than sixfold from 
$1.21 million the previous year. 
</P>
<P>
 The company attributed the surge to a turnaround in National Telephone & 
Communications (NTC), a subsidiary it acquired two years ago. NTC buys excess 
capacity on fiber-optic cable lines in bulk from major telephone companies. It 
then sells the phone capacity at discount prices to customers through a network 
of independent sales people, most of whom work from home. This sales system, 
introduced during the last six months, has doubled the number of NTC customers 
to 100,000, the company said. 
</P>
