</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Health Systems International Inc., the parent company of Woodland Hills-based 
Health Net and QualMed of Colorado, said its first-quarter profit surged 77% on 
a 17% increase in revenue compared with a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 For the three months ended March 31, the operator of the two health 
maintenance organizations reported a profit of $20.5 million, compared with a 
$11.6 million profit a year earlier. Revenue soared to $564.7 million, from 
$480.7 million. 
</P>
<P>
 Health Systems, created in January with the merger of Health Net and QualMed, 
said that on March 31 membership in its two HMOs totaled 1.41 million people, 
up 12% from a year earlier. Health Net and QualMed operate in six states. 
