<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; DEADLINE 
FOR QUAKE AID APPLICATIONS EXTENDED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The deadline to apply for disaster assistance under the Jan. 17 Northridge 
earthquake presidential declaration has been extended 60 days, to July 18. 
</P>
<P>
 Local, state and federal agencies are still receiving more than 1,600 
assistance applications daily at earthquake service centers or by phone, 
according to the Federal Emergency Management Agency and state Office of 
Emergency Services. 
</P>
<P>
 The deadline for the U.S. Small Business Administration's disaster loan 
program for individuals and businesses was also extended to July 18.  
</P>
<P>
 People not yet registered with FEMA for assistance may go to an earthquake 
service center or call (800) 462-9029, or (800) 462-7585 for the hearing- or 
speech-impaired.  
</P>
<P>
 People already registered who have questions may call (800) 525-0321, or (800) 
660-8005 for the hearing- or speech-impaired. 
</P>
</TEXT>
