METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; CUSTOMERS 
HELD HOSTAGE IN RESTAURANT ROBBERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A pair of gunmen briefly held 15 people hostage Monday during a robbery at a 
Los Angeles restaurant, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The holdup of Acapulco restaurant near Silver Lake occurred at 1 a.m., when 
two men stormed in and demanded the day's receipts, Sgt. J. J. Cerniglia said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police surrounded the restaurant, trapping the robbers inside, Cerniglia said. 
</P>
<P>
 When officers broke through the locked front door, one suspect tried to pass 
himself off as a customer but was arrested, police said. The other suspect 
fled. 
</P>
<P>
 A shot was fired by one of the gunmen during the holdup, but no one was 
injured, Cerniglia said. 
</P>
