<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; SPORTS 
GROUPS GET $148,206 PROMISED AFTER L.A. RIOTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Grants totaling $148,206 have been made to two Los Angeles youth sports 
organizations, fulfilling after nearly two years a promise by the Amateur 
Athletic Foundation to distribute $1 million in 1984 Olympic surplus funds in 
areas critically affected by the 1992 riots. 
</P>
<P>
 The grants of $100,035 to the Ketchum/Downtown YMCA and $48,171 to the Hoover 
Street Gym bring to $1,001,642 the amount of grants made by the foundation, 
which also distributes money to enhance youth sports throughout Southern 
California. 
</P>
