<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ANAHEIM; MAN PUSHING HIS CAR IS HIT FROM BEHIND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK I. PINSKY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 28-year-old Anaheim man pushing his disabled car on Ball Road was fatally 
injured Monday by a suspected hit-and-run driver, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Just after 5:30 a.m., Andres Garcia Lopez was pushing his disabled 1981 
Oldsmobile eastbound in the slow lane on Ball Road when he was hit from behind 
near East Street by a 1986 Toyota, driven by Omar Vasquez, 23, of Orange, Sgt. 
Richard Buchholz said. 
</P>
<P>
 Lopez was crushed between the two vehicles, but his wife, Maira Maras, 24, who 
was steering the disabled car, was not injured, Buchholz said. 
</P>
<P>
 As Vasquez left the scene, driving slowly eastbound on Ball as a result of 
collision damage, a witness shouted at him to pull over, Buchholz said. After 
Vasquez pulled over, the witness parked in front of the suspect's car until 
police arrived. 
</P>
<P>
 Vasquez was arrested on suspicion of felony hit-and-run driving and was booked 
into Anaheim City Jail. MARK I. PINSKY 
</P>
</TEXT>
