<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ANAHEIM; POLICE SUBSTATION APPROVAL EXPECTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTIN MILLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council today is expected to approve $120,000 in funding to open a 
Police Department mini-substation in the Anaheim Hills Festival Shopping 
Center. 
</P>
<P>
 The 2,300-square-foot facility at 8082 E. Santa Ana Canyon Road will feature a 
front-counter area, police briefing and changing rooms, and a meeting area with 
multimedia and teleconferencing capabilities. 
</P>
<P>
 Initially, the mini-substation will be open only from 11 a.m. to 1 p.m. and 
from 5 to 7 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The department has maintained an office with locker-room facilities for police 
officers serving in the canyon area since 1988. That facility, at another site, 
offered no direct service to the public. 
</P>
<P>
 The Police Department is exploring the possibility of opening a larger, 
full-service substation in Anaheim Hills later this year. MARTIN MILLER 
</P>
</TEXT>
