ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; CHP SEEKING MAN WHO BEAT MOTORIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK I. PINSKY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 California Highway Patrol officers are seeking help in locating a man they 
said beat a motorist who had stopped for a red light after exiting Interstate 
5. 
</P>
<P>
 A 44-year-old Mission Viejo man told officers that shortly before 11 a.m. 
Saturday he was beaten while stopped for a light at the freeway's southbound 
Avery Parkway off-ramp. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim, whom officers did not identify, said a man who might have exited 
the freeway behind him walked up to his car and began beating him through the 
driver's side window with a metal object, leaving him with a broken nose and 
other injuries requiring 35 stitches. 
</P>
<P>
 "He was cut up real bad," CHP spokesman Bruce Lian said. "This may have 
followed some sort of traffic dispute." 
</P>
<P>
 The CHP is looking for a man in his late 40s or early 50s, driving a white, 
late-model Honda Accord with a black covering over the front end. 
</P>
<P>
 Anyone with information is asked to contact Officer Dave Shisler at (714) 
661-6215. MARK I. PINSKY 
