<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO; BORDER PATROL ARRESTS 4 AFTER CHASE, 
CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK I. PINSKY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 U.S. Border Patrol agents arrested four Mexican nationals here Monday after a 
chase along Interstate 5 from the San Onofre checkpoint ended in a crash. 
</P>
<P>
 The four men ran the border checkpoint just after 6 a.m., according to Border 
Patrol spokeswoman Ann Summers. 
</P>
<P>
 The suspects' car crossed four lanes of traffic and exited the freeway at the 
El Camino Real off-ramp, but the car's brakes locked. The car skidded to the 
bottom of the ramp and hit a metal signpost in the 1700 block of South El 
Camino Real, Summers said. No one was injured. 
</P>
<P>
 After a short chase on foot, the car's driver, in the United States illegally, 
was arrested on suspicion of smuggling illegal immigrants. All four occupants 
are in custody, Summers said. 
</P>
<P>
 Because the freeway chase was in danger of becoming a "high-risk pursuit," 
Border Patrol agents behind the suspects' car had turned off their flashers, 
Summers said. MARK I. PINSKY 
</P>
