<P>
 Irvine Sensors Corp., a Costa Mesa developer of high density packages of 
computer electronics and infrared devices, reported a loss of $390,200, or 3 
cents a share, for its second quarter ended April 3, compared with a loss of 
$347,300, or 3 cents a share, for the like period last year.Revenue was up to 
$1.3 million from $940,400. For the first half, the company recorded a loss of 
$626,800, or 5 cents a share, compared with a loss of $789,100, or 6 cents a 
share, for the first six months of the previous fiscal year. Revenue rose to 
$2.6 million from $1.7 million. 
