<HEADLINE>
<P>
WHAT'S THE DEAL; FEEDING THAT CRAVING FOR ICE CREAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 When you absolutely must have ice cream, you can splurge or scrimp -- on both 
price and fat. Here's the cost to your wallet and your waist. 
</P>
<P>
 * Ben & Jerry's New York Super Fudge Chunk ice cream (chocolate flavor with 
pecans, walnuts, chocolate-covered almonds and white and dark chocolate 
chunks), 240 calories and 17 grams of fat per 4-ounce scoop, 63% fat, $1.70 
plus tax. 
</P>
<P>
 * Haagen-Dazs Caramel Cone Explosion bar, 350 calories and 23 grams of fat per 
93-gram bar, 59% fat, $3.95 for package of three. 
</P>
<P>
 * Jersey Maid Rocky Road ice milk, 100 calories and 2 grams of fat per 
half-cup serving, 18% fat, $2.89 for half a gallon. 
</P>
<P>
 * "My Cone," a 32-inch-by-24-inch poster of a little girl sitting under a tree 
holding a half-eaten cone with a drooling dog nearby, fat free, $12 at Prints 
Plus, Glendale Galleria. 
</P>
