<P>
138 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: EAST VALLEY; PUBLIC TO HEAR PLANS FOR HANSEN DAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIGUEL BUSTILLO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Los Angeles City Councilman Richard Alarcon is hosting a series of public 
meetings in the east San Fernando Valley on the future plans for the Hansen Dam 
as a recreational area. 
</P>
<P>
 The second of the five hearings, for residents of Sylmar and Mission Hills, 
will be held today at the Sylmar Recreation Center, 13109 Borden Ave., in 
Sylmar. 
</P>
<P>
 A meeting for Pacoima residents will take place Wednesday at the David M. 
Gonzales Recreational Center, 10945 Herrick Ave., in Pacoima. 
</P>
<P>
 The hearing for Sun Valley and North Hollywood residents is scheduled for the 
Sun Valley Recreation Center, 8133 Vineland Ave., in Sun Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 The final meeting, for Arleta, Van Nuys, North Hills and Panorama City 
residents, will take place at the Beachy Avenue School, 9757 Beachy Ave., 
Arleta. 
</P>
<P>
 All meetings begin at 7 p.m. MIGUEL BUSTILLO 
</P>
</TEXT>
