<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD: PRETORIA; OATH FOR MANDELA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nelson Mandela, the enduring symbol of the long struggle against apartheid, 
will be sworn in as South Africa's first black president today in a lavish 
ceremony at the Union Buildings, the government's administrative complex, in 
Pretoria.His inauguration will set in motion the transition to a new 
constitution for the country. He was formally elected president by the 
Parliament in Cape Town on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Mandela's inaugural address will be closely watched abroad for the tone and 
policy of his newborn administration. Among the dignitaries attending the 
inaugural will be U.S. Vice President Al Gore and First Lady Hillary Rodham 
Clinton, heading a large American contingent. 
</P>
